<TITLE> Mothers will get healthcare at home: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com)--The prime minister has said mothers will receive healthcare facilities, including family planning, at home, which will cut mortality rates for mothers and children. "We will reach healthcare to everyone's doorstep by launching community clinics," Sheikh Hasina said on Friday. "The government will allocate necessary money and resources to implement our campaign pledge to ensure people's healthcare," she said at a video conference with people having eye care at a three-day eye camp in Gopalganj. She asked about their treatment at the camp run under Begum Fazilatunnesa Mujib Eye Care Project at Bangabandhu Poverty Alleviation Training Complex at Kotalipara. The eye camp is being run under Begum Fazilatunnesa Mujib Eye Care Project at Bangabandhu Poverty Alleviation Complex at Kotalipara in Gopalganj. She said the government has taken necessary steps for the welfare of the country's neglected zones. Syed Modasser Ali, health adviser to the prime minister, central Awami League advisor Akram Uddin Ahmed, among others, spoke with her. bdnews24.c
